# Accepted Risks

This file is a project policy, not a todo list. Every rule is a deliberate
acceptance with a date when it MUST be re-reviewed.

## How to add a rule

1. Read `plugins/agentic-dev-team/knowledge/accepted-risks-schema.md` (lives in
   the plugin) — especially the rationale and expiry requirements.
2. Add an entry under `rules:` in the frontmatter above.
3. Commit with a message explaining the acceptance decision.

## How to remove a rule

Deleting a rule is a real decision. The commit message must state why the risk
is no longer accepted: fixed upstream, scoped out, moved to a runbook, etc.

## Broad rules

Rules with `broad: true` (wildcard `rule_id` or multi-file globs) get flagged
every run. Keep these narrow; prefer two scoped rules to one broad one.
